About Me



Hi! I'm Manami, a full-stack software engineer based in New York City. Originally from Chicago, I began my career in the tech industry as a Product Manager for a mobile application development company. Shortly after that, I moved to New York City and did platform sales at a AdTech company. Since then, I’ve hungered for more opportunities and decided that a move to New York City would further build my skills in business. Now holding three years of experience from the technology industry, I’ve realized that a company that places emphasis on an ethical and respectful environment, hold the best results in both employment and consumer revenue. This knowledge has served me beneficially in every sales team I have become a part of. However, sales was not enough for me—I wanted to form a deeper understanding of the technology I was selling and create a more authentic bond between the product and the customer, which then led me to enroll into a coding and computer science program. Now a recent graduate from Fullstack Academy, I have enhanced my knowledge on what it means to be a part of how a product is developed and the incredible feeling that comes with helping others understand the product from the ground up. Throughout my career thus far, I have continuously challenged myself for more—more experience, more knowledge, and more professional growth. That aside, when I’m not in the office, I can be found in the yoga studio or the kitchen. So if there’s a new studio in NYC to check out or a new recipe to explore, I am always more than happy to try out suggestions.



Technologies I've Worked With



Language: JavaScript (ES6+)

Frontend: React.js, Redux, HTML, CSS

Backend: Node.js, Express, Sequelize, PostgreSQL, Mongoose, MongoDB, RESTful API

DevOps: Heroku, Firebase, TDD (Mocha, Chai, Jasmine)

Tools: npm, GitHub, GIT, Visual Studio Code, Postman, Postico, Compass

); } export default AboutMe;
